923
01:20:34,872 --> 01:20:36,290
Were they Catholics?

924
01:20:37,250 --> 01:20:43,047
She isn't a nun. She's a lounge singer.
Her real name is Deloris Van Cartier.

925
01:20:43,256 --> 01:20:46,509
She witnessed a vicious crime
and has been hiding in our convent.

926
01:20:46,676 --> 01:20:49,011
- She isn't a nun?
- She lied to us?

927
01:20:49,178 --> 01:20:51,973
- But she was such a wonderful nun.
- Look what she did with the choir.

928
01:20:52,139 --> 01:20:54,809
- She made us sing beautifully.
- That should have tipped us.

929
01:20:54,976 --> 01:20:57,395
Well, I don't care who she is.
We can't sing without her!

930
01:20:57,562 --> 01:20:59,605
She's our inspiration.

931
01:20:59,772 --> 01:21:03,776
Reverend Mother. Please, I know that you
and Mary Clarence didn't always agree,

932
01:21:03,985 --> 01:21:06,153
- but we've gotta help her, please.
- We must save her.

933
01:21:06,362 --> 01:21:09,740
We can't leave it up to the feds.

934
01:21:10,741 --> 01:21:13,327
Calm down, calm down. Mary Robert.

935
01:21:13,536 --> 01:21:15,746
Think clearly. Have you any idea
who these two men were?

936
01:21:15,955 --> 01:21:20,751
Yes, they were from Reno and
they're taking her to the Moonlite Lounge.

937
01:21:20,960 --> 01:21:24,005
Reno, Nevada.

938
01:21:24,171 --> 01:21:26,632
Mary Emmanuel,
tell the monsignor the situation.

939
01:21:26,799 --> 01:21:29,635
- Yes, mother.
- The rest of you, follow me.

940
01:21:31,095 --> 01:21:34,223
It's 1,500 for the run to Reno.
That's 500 less than I normally charge.

941
01:21:34,390 --> 01:21:36,475
But we don't have $1,500.

942
01:21:36,642 --> 01:21:38,769
Well, then I can't fly you there.
I'm sorry.

943
01:21:40,354 --> 01:21:42,857
Look, I'm sorry. I've got some things
I have to check out here.

944
01:21:43,024 --> 01:21:46,402
Father, do not blame this young pilot
for abandoning us in our hour of need.

945
01:21:46,569 --> 01:21:50,364
When he stands before you on the day of
judgment, do not send straight him to hell.

946
01:21:50,573 --> 01:21:53,576
Please, do not treat him with
the same disregard that he's treated us.

947
01:21:53,743 --> 01:21:55,494
Just because he can't show
charity to nuns,

948
01:21:55,661 --> 01:21:58,205
try not to leave him without rewards
when he asks for them.

949
01:21:58,456 --> 01:22:00,082
We know it is easier
to answer the prayers

950
01:22:00,249 --> 01:22:02,126
of a man who has answered
the prayers of others,

951
01:22:02,293 --> 01:22:05,421
but if he should come to you
for relief of pain--

952
01:22:05,588 --> 01:22:09,216
Such as rheumatoid arthritis,
loss of hair, neck polyps.

953
01:22:09,425 --> 01:22:11,636
Don't leave him bald
and yowling in despair.

954
01:22:11,802 --> 01:22:14,138
Watch over him
as he refuses to watch over us.

955
01:22:14,388 --> 01:22:16,599
If you cannot, we know that you
will have done your best.

956
01:22:16,766 --> 01:22:20,227
- What goes around comes around.
- Sisters, sisters.

957
01:22:21,395 --> 01:22:23,022
Hold on a second.

958
01:22:41,666 --> 01:22:45,419
What did you think you were doing
running to the cops, Deloris? Hiding out?

959
01:22:46,045 --> 01:22:47,463
Big no-no, babe.

960
01:22:47,713 --> 01:22:49,382
Bet you're sorry now.

961
01:22:49,548 --> 01:22:54,011
I'm sorry for all my sins, Vince.
And I'm sorry for yours.

962
01:22:54,261 --> 01:22:56,555
I loved you, Deloris.

963
01:22:56,722 --> 01:22:58,641
I gave you everything.

964
01:22:58,808 --> 01:23:02,103
My affection, my time, a big-time career.

965
01:23:02,311 --> 01:23:05,106
And how do you repay me?
What's the thanks I get?

966
01:23:05,356 --> 01:23:09,735
Where's the loyalty?
You shouldn't have done that to me, babe.

967
01:23:09,902 --> 01:23:12,863
You'll be judged. We all will.

968
01:23:14,156 --> 01:23:16,033
I don't get judged

969
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:19,328
Vince, she's been acting weird
since we picked her up.

970
01:23:19,495 --> 01:23:22,331
It's like she's scared of nothing.

971
01:23:22,498 --> 01:23:26,293
She's scared.
Tell the boys how scared you are.

972
01:23:26,460 --> 01:23:28,629
I forgive you, Vince.

973
01:23:35,136 --> 01:23:36,804
Waste her.

974
01:23:46,897 --> 01:23:49,066
It's beautiful!

975
01:23:49,233 --> 01:23:52,111
And what a lovely name. Reno.

976
01:23:52,278 --> 01:23:54,447
And Gomorrah!

977
01:23:54,655 --> 01:23:57,074
She was this doll.
She used to wear fruit on her head and go:

978
01:23:57,241 --> 01:24:01,162
- Excuse me, Vince.
- Yeah.

979
01:24:01,454 --> 01:24:02,705
It's done?

980
01:24:02,872 --> 01:24:04,415
Not totally.

981
01:24:06,042 --> 01:24:10,463
- What's the problem?
- Vince, we can't waste a nun.

982
01:24:11,881 --> 01:24:16,552
What are you nuts talking about?
It's Deloris in a costume.

983
01:24:16,761 --> 01:24:19,138
Well, Vince, how do you know
she didn't join up

984
01:24:19,305 --> 01:24:21,390
and become a real nun
when she was there?

985
01:24:21,557 --> 01:24:22,933
Things like this happen.

986
01:24:25,853 --> 01:24:31,400
Because I know this woman in the biblical
sense and she ain't no nun.

987
01:24:31,609 --> 01:24:34,779
Now, I don't want to hear any more of this
Go in there and do it.

988
01:24:34,987 --> 01:24:36,572
Just don't come back till it's over.

989
01:24:37,073 --> 01:24:39,283
- Okay.
- It's done.

990
01:24:40,409 --> 01:24:43,788
- Okay, we go one, two, three, shoot.
- Wait.

991
01:24:43,954 --> 01:24:47,166
We don't go one, two,
and shoot on three?

992
01:24:47,333 --> 01:24:49,210
Get over there.

993
01:24:53,798 --> 01:24:57,551
One, two, three.

994
01:24:58,969 --> 01:25:01,597
- You didn't shoot.
- Neither did you.

995
01:25:01,764 --> 01:25:05,851
- I figured if you did, I wouldn't have to.
- That's what I figured.

996
01:25:07,853 --> 01:25:10,439
Sisters, come on!

997
01:25:14,527 --> 01:25:17,196
Deloris, we got it all worked out.

998
01:25:17,363 --> 01:25:19,657
- Strip.
- What?

999
01:25:19,824 --> 01:25:21,492
Come on, come on.
Take off the nun thing.

1000
01:25:21,659 --> 01:25:23,327
Yeah, yeah, the nun thing.

1001
01:25:23,536 --> 01:25:26,288
- What is she doing?
- Oh, my God. She's praying.

1002
01:25:26,497 --> 01:25:30,459
Lord, I want you to forgive
Willy and Joey.

1003
01:25:31,043 --> 01:25:33,879
Because they know not what they do.

1004
01:25:34,255 --> 01:25:36,507
They're only doing
what Vince told them to do.

1005
01:25:36,757 --> 01:25:39,385
Because Vince is too chicken
to do it himself.

1006
01:25:39,552 --> 01:25:43,556
So he's called upon these two men
to take care of his business.

1007
01:25:43,722 --> 01:25:46,308
So I want you to forgive them, Lord.

1008
01:25:55,651 --> 01:25:57,444
- Amen.
- Amen.

1009
01:26:12,793 --> 01:26:14,795
You all right? You all right?

1010
01:26:33,105 --> 01:26:35,941
- Go find Vince.
- Right.

1011
01:26:38,777 --> 01:26:42,781
Wait, wait, wait! Oh, my goodness.
There it is. The Moonlite Lounge.

1012
01:27:04,720 --> 01:27:10,309
Brace yourself, sisters.
Spread out and look for Mary Clarence.

1013
01:27:10,559 --> 01:27:13,312
Try to blend in.

1014
01:27:20,110 --> 01:27:21,904
Hi. Excuse me. Sorry.

1015
01:27:22,071 --> 01:27:25,115
Has anyone seen a nun?
A Carmelite nun? No? Sure?

1016
01:27:25,282 --> 01:27:28,118
No, she's not really a nun.
She's just posing as a nun.

1017
01:27:28,285 --> 01:27:29,745
It was a great shock to us--

1018
01:27:37,586 --> 01:27:40,339
Excuse me. Excuse me.
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

1019
01:27:40,547 --> 01:27:41,674
Place your bets.

1020
01:27:42,258 --> 01:27:43,676
Red 23.

1021
01:27:43,842 --> 01:27:46,303
Are you sure? How do you know?

1022
01:27:47,930 --> 01:27:49,807
- Red 23.
- Me too.

1023
01:27:49,974 --> 01:27:52,226
- Works for me.
- I'm on it.

1024
01:27:55,688 --> 01:27:57,064
Red 14.

1025
01:27:58,649 --> 01:28:00,901
I was just trying
to teach you all a lesson.

1026
01:28:02,945 --> 01:28:04,989
Oh, excuse me!

1027
01:28:12,830 --> 01:28:14,832
Sister Mary Ignatius!

1028
01:28:15,082 --> 01:28:16,875
Follow me.

1029
01:28:26,760 --> 01:28:27,845
Block off the street.

1030
01:28:28,012 --> 01:28:30,431
- But don't move in until I tell you.
- Okay.

1031
01:28:38,439 --> 01:28:41,191
- What are you doing here?
- We're saving you.

1032
01:28:42,234 --> 01:28:44,903
Mary Clarence, you're safe.

1033
01:28:45,362 --> 01:28:47,364
Come on, move, move.

1034
01:28:48,115 --> 01:28:50,326
Break! Now!

1035
01:28:52,661 --> 01:28:54,830
- Joey.
- Vinny. There's a thousand nuns here.

1036
01:28:54,997 --> 01:28:57,583
- What do we do?
- You go to the left. You go to the right.

1037
01:28:57,750 --> 01:28:59,335
- I'll go down the middle.
- All right.

1038
01:29:02,588 --> 01:29:04,965
Place your bets. Place your bets.

1039
01:29:22,483 --> 01:29:23,567
Hey, babe.

1040
01:29:25,486 --> 01:29:27,279
Yes, sweetheart?

1041
01:29:33,452 --> 01:29:36,580
Seal off the exits
and get ready to move in.

1042
01:29:38,582 --> 01:29:42,503
There's another way out.
Let's go. Come. Excuse us.

1043
01:30:01,980 --> 01:30:03,857
Move in now.

1044
01:30:06,402 --> 01:30:09,696
- I can't see a thing.
- Willy, hit the lights!

1045
01:30:13,283 --> 01:30:15,327
Freeze!

1046
01:30:15,536 --> 01:30:17,204
everybody!

1047
01:30:18,539 --> 01:30:20,249
Joey.

1048
01:30:20,791 --> 01:30:21,834
Where is she?

1049
01:30:22,376 --> 01:30:25,921
I'm right here. I'm here.

1050
01:30:26,088 --> 01:30:29,466
Leave them alone.
They don't have anything to do with it.

1051
01:30:29,633 --> 01:30:31,260
I'm here.

1052
01:30:34,721 --> 01:30:36,515
Calm down.

1053
01:30:46,525 --> 01:30:48,444
Joey,do it

1054
01:30:48,652 --> 01:30:52,739
I can't, Vince. She's still a nun.

1055
01:30:53,699 --> 01:30:57,453
She's a broad, you got it? Just a broad.

1056
01:30:57,661 --> 01:30:59,663
I guarantee you she is no broad.

1057
01:30:59,913 --> 01:31:02,207
She is Sister Mary Clarence
of Saint Katherine's Convent.

1058
01:31:02,416 --> 01:31:05,377
She's a model of generosity,
virtue and love.

1059
01:31:05,544 --> 01:31:08,172
You have my word for it, gentlemen.
She is a nun.

1060
01:31:09,047 --> 01:31:13,760
You hear that?
Now, aren't you glad we didn't shoot her?

1061
01:31:19,266 --> 01:31:20,559
- Don't shoot!
- Drop it.

1062
01:31:20,726 --> 01:31:21,935
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1063
01:31:22,436 --> 01:31:25,105
Guns down. Drop it, okay?

1064
01:31:25,272 --> 01:31:27,733
You all right? You okay?

1065
01:31:27,900 --> 01:31:29,485
Oh, God.

1066
01:31:32,613 --> 01:31:35,282
I'm shot! Watch the arm!

1067
01:31:35,449 --> 01:31:39,661
Are you okay? I'm sorry.
Things got kind of out of hand.

1068
01:31:39,870 --> 01:31:41,163
Oh, just kind of out of hand?

1069
01:31:41,330 --> 01:31:44,625
Boy, am I glad you're a much better shot
than you are a protector.

1070
01:31:45,751 --> 01:31:46,919
But...

1071
01:31:48,086 --> 01:31:49,379
Thank you.

1072
01:31:49,588 --> 01:31:51,924
- All right, come on.
- I was good to you.

1073
01:31:52,090 --> 01:31:55,594
We had a great thing!
You sang in a hotel! Badly!

1074
01:31:55,844 --> 01:31:57,804
How could you betray me like this?!

1075
01:31:58,055 --> 01:32:01,308
- You are nothing!
- Get him out of here.

1076
01:32:01,475 --> 01:32:04,686
- I got two words for you, Vince.
- Mary Clarence.

1077
01:32:06,980 --> 01:32:08,649
Bless you.

1078
01:32:09,316 --> 01:32:10,359
Let's go.

1079
01:32:10,526 --> 01:32:11,777
- Come on.
- Hey!

1080
01:32:13,111 --> 01:32:15,531
I hold you responsible for all of this.

1081
01:32:15,781 --> 01:32:17,908
For introducing a lounge act
into my convent.

1082
01:32:18,158 --> 01:32:23,205
For utterly disrupting our lives
and exposing us to mortal danger.

1083
01:32:24,873 --> 01:32:25,958
Thank you.

1084
01:32:30,128 --> 01:32:33,632
No, no, thank you. Thank you all.

1085
01:32:35,259 --> 01:32:36,760
I'm really gonna miss you guys.

1086
01:32:37,344 --> 01:32:40,389
We thought you were a nun, Deloris.

1087
01:32:41,265 --> 01:32:42,933
Van Cartier.

1088
01:32:47,646 --> 01:32:50,607
Sisters, we have a concert to do.

1089
01:32:51,024 --> 01:32:55,487
- I thought you were leaving.
- We can't both of us leave.